            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-10536",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "libcurl: libcurl: Use-after-free vulnerability leading to Denial of Service"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A use-after-free vulnerability exists in libcurl when an application\nconfigures an HTTP/2 stream-dependency tree via `CURLOPT_STREAM_DEPENDS` or\n`CURLOPT_STREAM_DEPENDS_E`, subsequently invokes `curl_easy_reset()`, and\nfinally terminates the handle with `curl_easy_cleanup()`. During this final\ncleanup phase, libcurl attempts to access and modify an internal structure\nthat was already freed during the reset operation."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-10536",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-10536\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: libcurl4t64\nFixed Version: 8.18.0-1ubuntu2.3\nLink: [CVE-2026-10536](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-10536)\nA use-after-free vulnerability exists in libcurl when an application\nconfigures an HTTP/2 stream-dependency tree via `CURLOPT_STREAM_DEPENDS` or\n`CURLOPT_STREAM_DEPENDS_E`, subsequently invokes `curl_easy_reset()`, and\nfinally terminates the handle with `curl_easy_cleanup()`. During this final\ncleanup phase, libcurl attempts to access and modify an internal structure\nthat was already freed during the reset operation.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-10536**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|libcurl4t64|8.18.0-1ubuntu2.3|[CVE-2026-10536](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-10536)|\n\nA use-after-free vulnerability exists in libcurl when an application\nconfigures an HTTP/2 stream-dependency tree via `CURLOPT_STREAM_DEPENDS` or\n`CURLOPT_STREAM_DEPENDS_E`, subsequently invokes `curl_easy_reset()`, and\nfinally terminates the handle with `curl_easy_cleanup()`. During this final\ncleanup phase, libcurl attempts to access and modify an internal structure\nthat was already freed during the reset operation."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "2.0",
                "tags": [
                  "vulnerability",
                  "security",
                  "LOW"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-11352",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "curl: libcurl: curl/libcurl: Remote denial of service via QUIC UDP receive function vulnerability"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An issue in curl’s QUIC UDP receive function allows a malicious HTTP/3 server\nto trigger a remote denial of service against a curl or libcurl client.\nBecause the helper function discards zero-length UDP datagrams before counting\nthem toward the per-call packet budget, a connected QUIC peer can continuously\nstream empty datagrams to indefinitely stall the client."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-11352",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-11352\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: libcurl4t64\nFixed Version: 8.18.0-1ubuntu2.3\nLink: [CVE-2026-11352](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-11352)\nAn issue in curl’s QUIC UDP receive function allows a malicious HTTP/3 server\nto trigger a remote denial of service against a curl or libcurl client.\nBecause the helper function discards zero-length UDP datagrams before counting\nthem toward the per-call packet budget, a connected QUIC peer can continuously\nstream empty datagrams to indefinitely stall the client.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-11352**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|libcurl4t64|8.18.0-1ubuntu2.3|[CVE-2026-11352](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-11352)|\n\nAn issue in curl’s QUIC UDP receive function allows a malicious HTTP/3 server\nto trigger a remote denial of service against a curl or libcurl client.\nBecause the helper function discards zero-length UDP datagrams before counting\nthem toward the per-call packet budget, a connected QUIC peer can continuously\nstream empty datagrams to indefinitely stall the client."
              },
