            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-35352",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "A Time-of-Check to Time-of-Use (TOCTOU) race condition exists in the m ..."
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A Time-of-Check to Time-of-Use (TOCTOU) race condition exists in the mkfifo utility of uutils coreutils. The utility creates a FIFO and then performs a path-based chmod to set permissions. A local attacker with write access to the parent directory can swap the newly created FIFO for a symbolic link between these two operations. This redirects the chmod call to an arbitrary file, potentially enabling privilege escalation if the utility is run with elevated privileges."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-35352",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-35352\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: rust-coreutils\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2026-35352](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-35352)\nA Time-of-Check to Time-of-Use (TOCTOU) race condition exists in the mkfifo utility of uutils coreutils. The utility creates a FIFO and then performs a path-based chmod to set permissions. A local attacker with write access to the parent directory can swap the newly created FIFO for a symbolic link between these two operations. This redirects the chmod call to an arbitrary file, potentially enabling privilege escalation if the utility is run with elevated privileges.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-35352**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|rust-coreutils||[CVE-2026-35352](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-35352)|\n\nA Time-of-Check to Time-of-Use (TOCTOU) race condition exists in the mkfifo utility of uutils coreutils. The utility creates a FIFO and then performs a path-based chmod to set permissions. A local attacker with write access to the parent directory can swap the newly created FIFO for a symbolic link between these two operations. This redirects the chmod call to an arbitrary file, potentially enabling privilege escalation if the utility is run with elevated privileges."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "5.5",
                "tags": [
