            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-35363",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "A vulnerability in the rm utility of uutils coreutils allows the bypas ..."
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A vulnerability in the rm utility of uutils coreutils allows the bypass of safeguard mechanisms intended to protect the current directory. While the utility correctly refuses to delete . or .., it fails to recognize equivalent paths with trailing slashes, such as ./ or .///. An accidental or malicious execution of rm -rf ./ results in the silent recursive deletion of all contents within the current directory. The command further obscures the data loss by reporting a misleading 'Invalid input' error, which may cause users to miss the critical window for data recovery."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-35363",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-35363\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: rust-coreutils\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2026-35363](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-35363)\nA vulnerability in the rm utility of uutils coreutils allows the bypass of safeguard mechanisms intended to protect the current directory. While the utility correctly refuses to delete . or .., it fails to recognize equivalent paths with trailing slashes, such as ./ or .///. An accidental or malicious execution of rm -rf ./ results in the silent recursive deletion of all contents within the current directory. The command further obscures the data loss by reporting a misleading 'Invalid input' error, which may cause users to miss the critical window for data recovery.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-35363**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|rust-coreutils||[CVE-2026-35363](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-35363)|\n\nA vulnerability in the rm utility of uutils coreutils allows the bypass of safeguard mechanisms intended to protect the current directory. While the utility correctly refuses to delete . or .., it fails to recognize equivalent paths with trailing slashes, such as ./ or .///. An accidental or malicious execution of rm -rf ./ results in the silent recursive deletion of all contents within the current directory. The command further obscures the data loss by reporting a misleading 'Invalid input' error, which may cause users to miss the critical window for data recovery."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "5.5",
                "tags": [
