            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-35364",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "A Time-of-Check to Time-of-Use (TOCTOU) race condition exists in the m ..."
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A Time-of-Check to Time-of-Use (TOCTOU) race condition exists in the mv utility of uutils coreutils during cross-device operations. The utility removes the destination path before recreating it through a copy operation. A local attacker with write access to the destination directory can exploit this window to replace the destination with a symbolic link. The subsequent privileged move operation will follow the symlink, allowing the attacker to redirect the write and overwrite an arbitrary target file with contents from the source."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-35364",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-35364\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: rust-coreutils\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2026-35364](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-35364)\nA Time-of-Check to Time-of-Use (TOCTOU) race condition exists in the mv utility of uutils coreutils during cross-device operations. The utility removes the destination path before recreating it through a copy operation. A local attacker with write access to the destination directory can exploit this window to replace the destination with a symbolic link. The subsequent privileged move operation will follow the symlink, allowing the attacker to redirect the write and overwrite an arbitrary target file with contents from the source.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-35364**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|rust-coreutils||[CVE-2026-35364](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-35364)|\n\nA Time-of-Check to Time-of-Use (TOCTOU) race condition exists in the mv utility of uutils coreutils during cross-device operations. The utility removes the destination path before recreating it through a copy operation. A local attacker with write access to the destination directory can exploit this window to replace the destination with a symbolic link. The subsequent privileged move operation will follow the symlink, allowing the attacker to redirect the write and overwrite an arbitrary target file with contents from the source."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "5.5",
                "tags": [
                  "vulnerability",
