            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-35373",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "A logic error in the ln utility of uutils coreutils causes the program ..."
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A logic error in the ln utility of uutils coreutils causes the program to reject source paths containing non-UTF-8 filename bytes when using target-directory forms (e.g., ln SOURCE... DIRECTORY). While GNU ln treats filenames as raw bytes and creates the links correctly, the uutils implementation enforces UTF-8 encoding, resulting in a failure to stat the file and a non-zero exit code. In environments where automated scripts or system tasks process valid but non-UTF-8 filenames common on Unix filesystems, this divergence causes the utility to fail, leading to a local denial of service for those specific operations."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-35373",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-35373\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: rust-coreutils\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2026-35373](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-35373)\nA logic error in the ln utility of uutils coreutils causes the program to reject source paths containing non-UTF-8 filename bytes when using target-directory forms (e.g., ln SOURCE... DIRECTORY). While GNU ln treats filenames as raw bytes and creates the links correctly, the uutils implementation enforces UTF-8 encoding, resulting in a failure to stat the file and a non-zero exit code. In environments where automated scripts or system tasks process valid but non-UTF-8 filenames common on Unix filesystems, this divergence causes the utility to fail, leading to a local denial of service for those specific operations.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-35373**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|rust-coreutils||[CVE-2026-35373](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-35373)|\n\nA logic error in the ln utility of uutils coreutils causes the program to reject source paths containing non-UTF-8 filename bytes when using target-directory forms (e.g., ln SOURCE... DIRECTORY). While GNU ln treats filenames as raw bytes and creates the links correctly, the uutils implementation enforces UTF-8 encoding, resulting in a failure to stat the file and a non-zero exit code. In environments where automated scripts or system tasks process valid but non-UTF-8 filenames common on Unix filesystems, this divergence causes the utility to fail, leading to a local denial of service for those specific operations."
              },
              "properties": {
