            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-39821",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "golang.org/x/net/idna: golang: golang.org/x/net/idna: Privilege escalation via incorrect Punycode label processing"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The ToASCII and ToUnicode functions incorrectly accept Punycode-encoded labels that decode to an ASCII-only label. For example, ToUnicode(\"xn--example-.com\") incorrectly returns the name \"example.com\" rather than an error. This behavior can lead to privilege escalation in programs using the idna package. For example, a program which performs privilege checks on the ASCII hostname may reject \"example.com\" but permit \"xn--example-.com\". If that program subsequently converts the ASCII hostname to Unicode, it will inadvertently permits access to the Unicode name \"example.com\"."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-39821",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-39821\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: golang.org/x/net\nFixed Version: 0.55.0\nLink: [CVE-2026-39821](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-39821)\nThe ToASCII and ToUnicode functions incorrectly accept Punycode-encoded labels that decode to an ASCII-only label. For example, ToUnicode(\"xn--example-.com\") incorrectly returns the name \"example.com\" rather than an error. This behavior can lead to privilege escalation in programs using the idna package. For example, a program which performs privilege checks on the ASCII hostname may reject \"example.com\" but permit \"xn--example-.com\". If that program subsequently converts the ASCII hostname to Unicode, it will inadvertently permits access to the Unicode name \"example.com\".",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-39821**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|golang.org/x/net|0.55.0|[CVE-2026-39821](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-39821)|\n\nThe ToASCII and ToUnicode functions incorrectly accept Punycode-encoded labels that decode to an ASCII-only label. For example, ToUnicode(\"xn--example-.com\") incorrectly returns the name \"example.com\" rather than an error. This behavior can lead to privilege escalation in programs using the idna package. For example, a program which performs privilege checks on the ASCII hostname may reject \"example.com\" but permit \"xn--example-.com\". If that program subsequently converts the ASCII hostname to Unicode, it will inadvertently permits access to the Unicode name \"example.com\"."
