            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-39824",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking integer overflow in NewNTUnicodeString in golang.org/x/sys/windows"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "NewNTUnicodeString does not check for string length overflow. When provided with a string that overflows the maximum size of a NTUnicodeString (a 16-bit number of bytes), it returns a truncated string rather than an error."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-39824",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-39824\nSeverity: UNKNOWN\nPackage: golang.org/x/sys\nFixed Version: 0.44.0\nLink: [CVE-2026-39824](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-39824)\nNewNTUnicodeString does not check for string length overflow. When provided with a string that overflows the maximum size of a NTUnicodeString (a 16-bit number of bytes), it returns a truncated string rather than an error.",
